## IV. Component and File Organization Rules (Naming Conventions)

These rules ensure a logical and navigable project structure using standard conventions.

| Rule ID | Item Type | Naming Convention | Example |
| :---: | :---: | :---: | :--- |
| **R14** | **Directories/Folders** | `kebab-case` | `src/components/user-card/` |
| **R15** | **Component Files/Classes** | `PascalCase` | `UserProfile.js`, `class UserProfile { ... }` |
| **R16** | **Utility/General Files** | `camelCase` or `kebab-case` | `src/utils/formatDate.js` |
| **R17** | **Constants** | `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` | `export const MAX_ITEMS = 10;` |
| **R18** | **Co-location** | Match component name | Component-specific files (e.g., styles, tests) should live within the component's folder (e.g., `UserCard/UserCard.css`). |

---

## V. Client/Server Division (Domain Separation)

The project is logically divided into client-side and server-side domains.

* **Client (Front-end):** UI components, user-interaction logic, features, presentation.
* **Server (Back-end):** Database config, controllers, routing, server configuration, API business logic.